<title>
Valve Lash (Clearance) Inspection
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove negative cable at battery.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove cylinder head cover referring to 
<intxref refid = "S8T40A1456048">Cylinder Head Cover Removal and Installation:F9Q</intxref>
.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Turn crankshaft pulley (1) clockwise until cam lobe (2) becomes perpendicular to tappet face (3) at valves &#8220;1&#8221; and &#8220;6&#8221; as shown in figure.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Check valve lashes with thickness gauge (4) according to the following procedure.
</ptxt>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Check valve lashes at valves &#8220;1&#8221; and &#8220;6&#8221;.
</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Turn camshaft by 90&#176; by turning crankshaft pulley with wrench.
</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Make sure that cam lobe is perpendicular to tappet face at valves to be checked (in this case, &#8220;5&#8221; and &#8220;8&#8221;), if not, adjust camshaft position by turning crankshaft pulley. Check valve lashes.
</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
In the same manner as b) &#8211; c), check valve lashes at valves &#8220;4&#8221; and &#8220;7&#8221;.
</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
In the same manner as b) &#8211; c) again, check valve lashes at valves &#8220;2&#8221; and &#8220;3&#8221;.
</ptxt>
</s2>
<ptxt>
If valve lash (clearance) is out of specification, record valve lash (clearance) and adjust it to specification referring to 
<intxref refid = "S8T40A1454004">Valve Lash (Clearance) Adjustment:F9Q</intxref>
.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<spec-sdm>
<sdm-title>
Valve lash (clearance) specification
</sdm-title>
<sdm1>
<sdm-condition>
When cold
</sdm-condition>
<sdm2>
<sdm-condition>
Intake
</sdm-condition>
<sdm-value>
0.15 &#8211; 0.25 mm (0.0060 &#8211; 0.0098 in.)
</sdm-value>
</sdm2>
<sdm2>
<sdm-condition>
Exhaust
</sdm-condition>
<sdm-value>
0.35 &#8211; 0.45 mm (0.0138 &#8211; 0.0177 in.)
</sdm-value>
</sdm2>
</sdm1>
</spec-sdm>
